{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P3TJDGm7FbJaWExf1nNySd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The readiness probe is timing out because the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` variable is not being interpolated in the shell command (it's in a exec array not shell expansion). Let me fix the readiness probe.\n\nAlso, the cluster is having \"timed out while waiting for initial discovery state\" - this is because only one pod is up and it's waiting for the others to form the cluster. The StatefulSet creates pods sequentially, but only starts the next pod once the previous is Ready. Since es-0 is not Ready, es-1 and es-2 never start.\n\nI need to fix two things:\n1. The readiness probe env var issue - the exec form doesn't do shell variable expansion, so I need to wrap the curl command with `/bin/sh -c` to enable variable substitution\n2. Allow pods to start even if the previous pod is not ready, so the cluster can form\n\nFor the probe, I'm using a shell command that curls the Elasticsearch health endpoint with basic auth credentials and checks if the status is green or yellow. The ELASTIC_PASSWORD variable should expand within the shell context, though the Kubernetes event message might display it unexpanded. The real problem could be that curl is timing out rather than the variable expansion itself.\n\nI'm realizing the core issue is a bootstrap deadlock: es-0 is running but can't become Ready because it's waiting for the other nodes to form a quorum, but es-1 and es-2 can't start until es-0 is Ready. Since `cluster.initial_master_nodes` requires at least 2 of the 3 nodes to be up, I need to change the StatefulSet to use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods start simultaneously instead of sequentially.\n\nFor the readiness probe, the real problem is that it's checking cluster health which returns 503 until the cluster is formed. I should simplify it to just verify that Elasticsearch is listening on port 9200, letting the pods come up and form the cluster without waiting for health checks to pass. Also need to verify the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable is actually being passed to the container so the curl command expands properly.\n\nSince I can't modify `podManagementPolicy` on an existing StatefulSet, I'll need to delete and recreate it with `Parallel` policy so all pods start simultaneously instead of sequentially.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1641,"cache_read_input_tokens":33649,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1641},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d34880d-99c1-4388-acec-e3aedf6a2393","uuid":"0bff2376-dfbf-44c2-849d-ad5bf64b44f8","request_id":"req_011CcMaTNk4DnaxLFWgg3iS1"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P3TJDGm7FbJaWExf1nNySd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear: `podManagementPolicy` defaults to `OrderedReady`, so `es-1`/`es-2` wait for `es-0` to be Ready — but `es-0` can't pass readiness until the cluster forms with quorum. Classic bootstrap deadlock. I need to set `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` and fix the readiness probe."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1641,"cache_read_input_tokens":33649,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1641},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d34880d-99c1-4388-acec-e3aedf6a2393","uuid":"8cab4d92-9250-4b6b-9527-c2565c365d39","request_id":"req_011CcMaTNk4DnaxLFWgg3iS1"}
